== Turmeric Brown Rice ==

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in a small #pot{} over medium heat. Stir in @turmeric{1%tsp} until combined.

Stir in @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, @water{3/4%cup}, and a big pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to use in Step 5.

> Swap in brown rice for jasmine rice; use 1¾ cups water (3½ cups for 4 servings) and a pinch of salt. Cook for 20-25 minutes. (Save jasmine rice for another use.)

== White Sauce ==

Meanwhile, bring @butter{2%tbsp} to room temperature. Wash and dry produce.

Quarter @lemon{1}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Trim and finely dice half the @cucumber{1}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{3%tbsp}, @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}, @garlic powder{1%tsp}, and a squeeze of lemon juice. Add water 1 tsp at a time until sauce reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with @salt and @pepper.

== Shawarma-Spiced Ground Turkey ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and cook until fragrant, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Add @ground turkey{10%oz}, @shawarma spice blend{1%tbsp}, @salt{1/2%tsp}, and pepper. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> Ground Turkey is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{3} and @water{1/4%cup}. Reduce heat to medium low and simmer until slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

== Assembly ==

Fluff rice with a fork; stir in @sliced almonds{1/2%oz} and half the scallion greens. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

Toast @whole wheat pitas{2}, then spread with softened @butter{3%tbsp}. Cut each pita into four wedges.

Divide rice between #bowls{}. Top with turkey and diced cucumber in separate sections; sprinkle diced cucumber with a pinch of salt.

Drizzle turkey with @hot sauce{2%tsp} to taste. Drizzle white sauce over bowls; garnish with remaining scallion greens. Serve with pitas and remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> TIP: If you like, scoop up some of the rice, turkey, diced cucumber, and sauces with the pita and eat it all in one bite!